node.text: It was a beautiful day and I’m in love with my new daughter-in-law. Check out this video shot and produced by Stephen Norregaard. See the full wide format version here: https://vimeo.com/308998543

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jean Stoffer on July 19, 2021 tagging @johnstoffer, @maurastoffer, @stofferhome, and @stofferhomecabinetry. May be an image of kitchen.

node.text: When the formal dining room became the kitchen @johnstoffer and @maurastoffer ‘s “new” house. Make sure you swipe through to see the before! This gorgeous island is a custom design and the range alcove is from @stofferhomecabinetry in Cotswold Green. “Longbridge” pulls available @stofferhome  John sent me a folder with some more great pics and I can’t wait to show them to you!

node.text: I used to call it my office. Now I call it my Zoom Room. Anybody else in the same boat?  Always making sure what’s behind you looks ok?

node.text: We combined the dining room and kitchen in the #jsdpaintedbrick project to make a space where there is plenty of room for the family to hang out together. The kitchen is where everyone ends up. Am I right?? But because we all need a stash space, we used this little corner for a jewel of a walk-in pantry. @stofferhomecabinetry in natural Oak, Birmingham and Cotswold Green. “Monroe” pulls and “Thatcher” knobs, lighting and “Endeavor” art from @stofferhome

node.text: It’s a big day, a happy day!  The brand new @magnolianetwork is live today!  A new project is coming soon, but in the meantime, head to @discoveryplus to stream my episode of #PointOfView on @magnolianetwork #MagnoliaNetwork

node.text: I love this whole set up at The Madison!  The interior windows were old storm windows on the sun porch and repurposed here. The millwork was patiently restored and replaced by @kenowabuilders using material from @the_empire_co  There really are true craftsmen out there, and I feel so grateful they worked at The Madison where I can enjoy the fruit of their labor every day. Photographed by @stofferphotographyinteriors Light fixture from @stofferhome

node.text: Would ya look at what I just found!  A great old house in need.  I might have to get involved. Actually, I just bought it! 😍 Anybody ready to join me for a slow flip?  I’ll be trying out some new things in this old beauty. What would you guys like to see first?  UPDATE!  Going live today (7/4) at 4 pm Eastern with a walk through!

node.text: Check out the bar at our newest project #johnandmaura. @johnstoffer and @maurastoffer offer hospitality in spades when they make drinks. Whether it’s the morning latte or the evening craft cocktail, they make people (us 😊) feel loved and welcome. And so this little set up with fridge drawers is just the best for them. And guess what?  We loved this color (Plymouth Green) so much we decided to make it a new @stofferhomecabinetry color intro. What do you think?  Oh, and the tambour detailing is amazing, right?  And do you see the tiny alabaster light fixture on the wall to the right?  I love that. Thanks for the photo @johnstoffer ❤️

node.text: There is a lot to talk about in this pic of our newest project. First it’s near and dear as it belongs to @JohnStoffer and @MauraStoffer. So our project hashtag is #johnandmaura They recently bought a beautiful old English home. Details everywhere. Just amazing. When they asked if I would help with the kitchen I was like “when can we start?” And when I saw the house’s layout I asked them what they thought about moving the kitchen into the formal dining room and cutting out an archway into the living room.  They were all in from the start. Here’s the view from the living room. There is a lot more to talk about (hello gorgeous island) but for now, enjoy the view and while you’re at it: start thinking about YOUR formal dining room… What if… Thanks for the pic @JohnStoffer Range wall Cabinetry in Cotswold green  from @stofferhomecabinetry
